.Dd January 20, 2009
.Dt SND_DAVBUS 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm snd_davbus
.Nd "Apple Davbus audio device driver"
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To compile this driver into the kernel,
place the following lines in your
kernel configuration file:
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "device sound"
.Cd "device snd_davbus"
.Ed
.Pp
Alternatively, to load the driver as a
module at boot time, place the following line in
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
snd_davbus_load="YES"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver provides support for the Apple Davbus audio controllers found in
many G3-era Apple machines.
.Sh HARDWARE
Chips supported by the
.Nm
driver include:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Apple Burgundy Audio
.It
Apple Screamer Audio
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr snd_ai2s 4 ,
.Xr sound 4
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
device driver appeared in
.Fx 8.0 .
.Sh AUTHORS
.An -nosplit
The
.Nm
driver was written by
.An Marco Trillo Aq Mt marcotrillo@gmail.com .
.Sh BUGS
Recording is not currently supported.
